    "body": "### Problem\n\nRight now, in `start_timer`, the buffer handling is inconsistent.\n\nThe timer captures a buffer (`buf`) when it is created, but later during cleanup, it reads from `ui.bufs.msg` instead of using the same buf.\n\nWhen this happens:\n- The timer modifies the original buffer (`buf`)\n- But the cleanup check is performed on `ui.bufs.msg`\n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nStep 1\nBuild and start Neovim with ui2 enabled\n\nStep 2\nRun this lua code snippet \n\n```\nlocal api = vim.api\n\n-- create buffers\nlocal old_buf = api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\nlocal new_buf = api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\n\n-- simulate ui state\nlocal ui = { bufs = { msg = new_buf } }\n\n-- set content like a real case\napi.nvim_buf_set_lines(old_buf, 0, -1, false, { \"message\", \"\" })\n\n-- simulate mutation (like set_text)\napi.nvim_buf_set_text(old_buf, 0, 0, 0, 7, {})\n\napi.nvim_buf_set_lines(new_buf, 0, -1, false, {\"DIFFERENT\"})\n\n-- BUG: checking wrong buffer\nlocal wrong = api.nvim_buf_get_lines(ui.bufs.msg, 0, 1, false)[1]\nprint(\"wrong buffer line:\", wrong)\n\n-- CORRECT: checking right buffer\nlocal correct = api.nvim_buf_get_lines(old_buf, 0, 1, false)[1]\nprint(\"correct buffer line:\", correct)\n```\n\nStep 3\nObserve the message area, you'll find  modification happens on `old buf` but the current logic reads from `ui.bufs.msg` (`new_buf`), which tells that the check is being performed on a different buffer than the one that was modified\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIf the timer modifies a buffer (buf), any subsequent checks (like verifying empty lines) should also be performed on that same buffer\nThe cleanup logic should not depend on ui.bufs.msg, since that buffer can change before the timer executes\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.9.5\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nI don't think Vim shows the same issue\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 24.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGNOME Terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nDownloaded prebuilt binary from Neovim releases page",
